Source: netperfmeter
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Thomas Dreibholz <dreibh@iem.uni-due.de>
Homepage: http://www.iem.uni-due.de/~dreibh/netperfmeter/
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), autotools-dev, libsctp-dev (>= 1.0.5), libbz2-dev (>= 1.0)
Standards-Version: 3.8.1

Package: scalartools
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: r-base
Description: Scalar File Processing Tools
 This package contains tools to create GNU R data tables from scalar files and
 to combine such tables. On-the-fly BZip2-decompression and compression is
 supported to reduce storage space.

Package: netperfmeter
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, scalartools, r-base, ghostscript, fntsample, pdftk, ghostscript
Replaces: netmeter (<= 0.5.1)
Conflicts: netmeter (<= 0.5.1)
Recommends: traceroute, iputils-tracepath, iputils-ping, rsplib-tools, subnetcalc (>= 2.0.2)
Description: Network Performance Meter
 NetPerfMeter is a network performance meter for the UDP, TCP, SCTP and
 DCCP transport protocols. It simultaneously transmits bidirectional
 flows to an endpoint and measures the resulting flow bandwidths. The
 results are written as vector and scalar files. The vector files can
 be used to create PDF plots of the results.
